Add multi-force particle physics: Coulomb, scaffold attraction, collision toggle

Physics forces (each with own method, enable flag, strength and range):
- Collision: hard-sphere bounce, now togglable via collisionEnabled
- Attraction: linear short-range inter-particle pull
- Spring: linear charge-dependent inter-particle force
- Coulomb: 1/r^2 charge-dependent inter-particle force (new)
- Scaffold: spring pull toward saved origin positions (new)

Per-particle charge (float) and originIdx (int16_t) link particles
to their scaffold positions for position/color restoration.

textToParticles and screenToParticles now default to:
- collisionEnabled = false (particles dont bump each other)
- scaffoldEnabled = true, strength 1.0, range 10.0
  (text wiggles with temperature but holds shape)

Renamed _particleInteraction -> _interParticleInteraction.
Added _scaffoldInteraction() as separate loop (particle to origin).

OSC: 26 positional args for /display/N/particles config.
GUI: Collision checkbox, Coulomb row, Scaffold row, all state synced.
Docs: comprehensive particle system command documentation.
